# Encoding and Korean text

- Save all source files as **UTF-8** (no ANSI, EUC-KR, or other legacy encodings).
- **Do not change** existing Korean UI copy, Korean variable names, or translation strings unless the user explicitly asks.
- When editing, avoid replacing large regions of a file in ways that re-save mojibake; if Korean appears as `?` or garbage, restore from git history (`git show <commit>:path`) and re-apply edits using tools that preserve UTF-8 (e.g. read/write the file as UTF-8 in Node, not lossy clipboard or mis-encoded shell redirects).
- Extra care: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `client.tsx`, components under `src/components/`, and JSON with user-facing text.
